.IX Title "Jifty::Plugin::EditInPlace::Action::FileEditor 3"
.TH Jifty::Plugin::EditInPlace::Action::FileEditor 3 "2006-05-25" "perl v5.8.8" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.SH "NAME"
Jifty::Plugin::EditInPlace::Action::FileEditor
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This action allows you to edit mason components (and eventually libraries)
using Jifty's \fIAction\fR system.  It should only be enabled when you're
running Jifty in \f(CW\*(C`DevelMode\*(C'\fR. 
.SH "WARNING"
.IX Header "WARNING"
\&\fB\s-1THIS\s0 \s-1ACTION\s0 \s-1LETS\s0 \s-1YOU\s0 \s-1REMOTELY\s0 \s-1EDIT\s0 \s-1EXECUTABLE\s0 \s-1CODE\s0\fR.
.PP
\&\fB\s-1THIS\s0 \s-1IS\s0 \s-1DANGEROUS\s0\fR
.Sh "new"
.IX Subsection "new"
Create a new \f(CW\*(C`FileEditor\*(C'\fR action.
.Sh "arguments"
.IX Subsection "arguments"
Sets up this action's arguments.
.IP "path" 4
.IX Item "path"
Where to save the file
.IP "file_type" 4
.IX Item "file_type"
(One of mason_component or library)
.IP "source_path" 4
.IX Item "source_path"
Where to read the file from.
.IP "destination_path" 4
.IX Item "destination_path"
Where to write the file to. If the current user can't write to 
the source_path, defaults to something inside the app's directory.
.IP "content" 4
.IX Item "content"
The actual content of the file we're editing.
.Sh "get_default_content"
.IX Subsection "get_default_content"
Finds the version of the \f(CW\*(C`source_path\*(C'\fR (of type \f(CW\*(C`file_type\*(C'\fR) and
loads it into \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR.
.Sh "validate_destination_path \s-1PATH\s0"
.IX Subsection "validate_destination_path PATH"
Returns true if the user can write to the directory \f(CW\*(C`PATH\*(C'\fR. False
otherwise. Should be refactored to a \f(CW\*(C`path_writable\*(C'\fR routine and a
trivial validator.
.Sh "take_action"
.IX Subsection "take_action"
Writes the \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR out to the \f(CW\*(C`destination_path\*(C'\fR.
